The paper focuses on evaluating the effectiveness of convolutional neural network (CNN) features for object recognition and detection tasks, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning architectures such as AlexNet and VGGNet also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of principal component analysis, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
